claims:
1. A method for additive manufacturing using releasable inks on a substrate mold, comprising:
applying a surface treatment to a surface of a mold, the mold defining an article for manufacturing;
depositing an ink including particles of a trace material onto the surface treatment, the particles coated with a functionalization agent based on a surface energy of the surface treatment;
curing the deposited ink to evaporate a solvent carrier;
sintering the deposited ink to form a continuous trace of material;
molding the article by adding a molding substance to the mold over the trace; and
releasing the molded article from the mold, the trace adhering to either the mold or the article based on the functionalization agent providing the trace greater adhesion to the mold or the article.

17. A method of forming a circuit on or within a molded substrate, comprising:
printing a trace pattern defining a circuit on a mold surface;
molding the substrate by injecting a molten material into the mold;
removing the molded substrate from the mold, the trace pattern defining the circuit releasing from the mold surface and adhering to the molded substrate based on a greater adhesion between the trace and the substrate than between the trace and the mold surface.

20. A selective release molding apparatus for additive manufacturing using releasable inks on a substrate mold, comprising:
a mold having a molding surface responsive to receiving a surface treatment, the mold defining an article for manufacturing;
an application mechanism for depositing an ink including particles of a trace material onto the surface treatment, the particles coated with a functionalization agent injection based on a surface energy of the surface treatment;
a heating source configured for, following a period for curing the deposited ink to evaporate a solvent carrier, sintering the deposited ink to form a continuous trace of material; and
an injection molding nozzle configured to mold the article by extruding a molding substance to the mold over the trace, the treated mold surface responsive to release the molded article from the mold, the trace adhering to either the mold or the article based on the functionalization agent providing the trace greater adhesion to the mold or the article.
